text: I really enjoyed the food, especially the bold and spicy flavors. Initially, I thought the prices were a bit high, but considering the generous portion sizes, they seem reasonable. However, be cautious when ordering, as the portions are typically large enough to serve two people. The dishes were slightly oily, which added to their richness and taste
Excellent food every time I visit. I love that we can request for no garlic, no coriander, less spicy etc and it's always well executed
I've ogone here twice since the maocai is great. It is not a spicy type. A waitress recommended another dish today, tricolor beef, which is very tasty. You can actually taste three flavors!

Heard good things about the place and decided to try with a few friends. Service was good but food was average as most of the dishes were overly salty in my opinion. Could be a matter of personal preference.

Food: 3.5-Stars to 4-Stars: good selection of Sichuan & Hui tasting foods (not hala as have pork). Price is slightly higher in relative to the other PRC food in the area, but not alot

3.5-Star: for everything else

Others: more for cooked food and not BBQ Sticks
